# Cursor Rules — Connect Four (Compose HTML)

## Project
Kotlin Multiplatform project using Compose HTML. The game lives in `composeApp/src/webMain/`.
Platform-specific entrypoints are in `jsMain/` and `wasmJsMain/`. Tests go in `webTest/`.

## Language & Framework
- All code is **Kotlin**. Do not write JavaScript, TypeScript, or HTML files.
- UI is built with **Compose HTML** (`org.jetbrains.compose.web.dom.*`, `org.jetbrains.compose.web.css.*`).
- Do not use Compose Multiplatform canvas/desktop APIs. Use DOM-based Compose HTML only.
- Style with `StyleSheet` objects and `style {}` blocks. No external CSS files.

## Architecture Rules
- Keep game logic **completely pure** — no Compose imports in `GameLogic.kt` or `GameState.kt`.
- `GameState` is a data class. All mutations return a new copy.
- Side effects (localStorage, animations) belong in Composables or dedicated service objects, never in logic files.
- Use `remember { mutableStateOf(...) }` for all UI state. Do not use global mutable variables.

## Code Style
- Prefer `val` over `var` everywhere possible.
- Name Composable functions with PascalCase, pure functions with camelCase.
- Keep each file under ~150 lines. Split if it grows larger.
- Write self-documenting code; only add comments for non-obvious logic.

## Do Not
- Do not add new Gradle dependencies without asking.
- Do not modify `build.gradle.kts`, `settings.gradle.kts`, or `gradle.properties`.
- Do not create `.html`, `.css`, or `.js` files.
- Do not use `kotlinx.coroutines` unless explicitly instructed.
- Do not implement features not listed in `PROGRESS.md`.
